The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu has cancelled the 13th edition of its annual birthday colloquium to honour the victims of the Kaduna train attack. Tinubu who clocks 70th today, March 29th made the announcement at Eko Hotels in Lagos, the venue of the 13th Bola Ahmed Tinubu Colloquium with the theme, ‘Pivoting Nigeria Into The New Order’. According to him, the attack was a “national tragedy” and over 60 persons lost their lives to the terror. Details later…